<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><span class="doxyHighlight">DWARFDebugLine::ParsingState::SpecialOpcodeDelta</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><span class="doxyHighlight">DWARFDebugLine::ParsingState::handleSpecialOpcode(uint8&#95;t Opcode,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                                  uint64&#95;t OpcodeOffset) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A special opcode value is chosen based on the amount that needs</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to be added to the line and address registers. The maximum line</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// increment for a special opcode is the value of the line&#95;base</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// field in the header, plus the value of the line&#95;range field,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// minus 1 (line base + line range - 1). If the desired line</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// increment is greater than the maximum line increment, a standard</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// opcode must be used instead of a special opcode. The &quot;address</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// advance&quot; is calculated by dividing the desired address increment</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// by the minimum&#95;instruction&#95;length field from the header. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// special opcode is then calculated using the following formula:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  opcode = (desired line increment - line&#95;base) +</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//           (line&#95;range &#42; address advance) + opcode&#95;base</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00749" /><CodeLine lineNumber="749"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If the resulting opcode is greater than 255, a standard opcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00750" /><CodeLine lineNumber="750"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// must be used instead.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// To decode a special opcode, subtract the opcode&#95;base from the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// opcode itself to give the adjusted opcode. The amount to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// increment the address register is the result of the adjusted</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// opcode divided by the line&#95;range multiplied by the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// minimum&#95;instruction&#95;length field from the header. That is:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  address increment = (adjusted opcode / line&#95;range) &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                      minimum&#95;instruction&#95;length</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The amount to increment the line register is the line&#95;base plus</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the result of the adjusted opcode modulo the line&#95;range. That is:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// line increment = line&#95;base + (adjusted opcode % line&#95;range)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><span class="doxyHighlight">  DWARFDebugLine::ParsingState::OpcodeAdvanceResults AddrAdvanceResult =</span></CodeLine>
